item.title: Kayla add a quote by Albert Camus
item.description: "Don't walk behind me; I may not lead. Don't walk in front of me; I may not follow. Just walk beside me and be my friend." -- Albert Camus

item.title: Kayla add a quote by Dr. Seuss
item.description: "Don't cry because it's over, smile because it happened." -- Dr. Seuss

item.title: Kayla add a quote by Stone Sour
item.description: "Freedom's just a word today Freedom's just a word When someone takes your word away It's seldom ever heard So take a sentence full of things you're not supposed to say Carry on, but don't write them down or you'll be gone" -- Stone Sour

item.title: Kayla add a quote by Friedrich Nietzsche
item.description: "Without music, life would be a mistake." -- Friedrich Nietzsche

item.title: Kayla add a quote by Douglas Adams
item.description: "I love deadlines. I love the whooshing noise they make as they go by." -- Douglas Adams

item.title: Kayla add a quote by Elvis Costello
item.description: "Writing about music is like dancing about architecture - it's really a stupid thing to want to do." -- Elvis Costello

item.title: Kayla add a quote by Nine Inch Nails
item.description: "What have I become? My sweetest friend; everyone I know goes away in the end. And you could have it all: my empire of dirt. I will let you down. I will make you hurt." -- Nine Inch Nails

item.title: Kayla add a quote by Leopold Stokowski
item.description: "A painter paints pictures on canvas. But musicians paint their pictures on silence." -- Leopold Stokowski

item.title: Kayla add a quote by Maya Angelou
item.description: "Most people don't grow up. Most people age. They find parking spaces, honor their credit cards, get married, have children, and call that maturity. What that is, is aging." -- Maya Angelou
